		{
			description: [
				""
				""
				"1. Put iron ore and a crucible into the blast furnace."
				""
				"2. Wait for the ore to melt into an ingot inside the crucible."
				""
				"3. Pour the molten metal into a casting mold."
				""
				"4. Craft an iron anvil and a forging hammer."
				""
				"5. Repeat steps 1, 2, and 3."
				""
				"6. Heat the obtained ingot in a forge (put coal in the forge, then the ingot, and wait until the metal turns red-hot)."
				""
				"7. Place the heated ingot on the anvil and hold the hammer in your hand."
				""
				"8. Press the Y key to open the ingot editor. Fill the green squares with metal. Use the mouse wheel to change the forging direction."
				""
				"9. When all the green squares are filled, select the strike mode (Y) and remove excess metal by right-clicking."
				""
				"10. Take the finished pickaxe head and quench it in water."
				""
				"11. Right-click on the grindstone."
				""
				"12. Craft the pickaxe. — Done!"
			]
			id: "302CF35A993C49DD"
